The conditions of the sale and with which Mr Ball is to be charged, are that he is to pay for the land £800 (which it cost me) with Interest at the rate of 6 perCent per Annum, from the first day of August 1789 (being the day on which Mr Dandridge conveyed the land to me) until it is discharged.- That on or before the 10th day of April 1798 he is to pay me £303 and to give a mortgage on the land as a security for the payment of the residue of the purchase money with Interest as aforesaid in two equal annual Installments.- whereupon I have obliged myself my heirs &c to convey the land to him or to his assigns with a warrentee against any person claiming under me or the said John Dandridge, but no others -
